 and a particular vector 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{b}$
\end_inset

, we can use row reduction to determine whether a solution of 
\begin_inset Formula $M\mathbf{v}=\mathbf{b}$
\end_inset

 exists and find it if it does, but we have no way to tell ahead of time
 whether a solution will exist.
 Nor do we have an efficient way of finding all the solutions when there
 are more than one.
